events.name: talk.js DevFest.Asia Edition
events.description: This event is part of DevFest.Asia, Southeast Asia's first community organized web developer festival. Please RSVP here instead. The next talk.js will be on Tuesday 17th November. This is a special edition of talk.js in conjunction with DevFest.Asia and <a>JSConf.Asia</a>. We have a special speaker from Australia and the talks will be longer and more in depth than usual. Do join us for this special occasion! Scheduled Talks: • Cold War: City State - Simon Swain Cold War is a exploration of simulation and graphics. We will dive in to smooth 60fps animation in the browser using html5 canvas, and see how much juice we can squeeze out of our systems. This session will also premiere the Cold War platform, giving you examples and tools for you to produce simulations based on the concepts in the talk. • Building Space Radar with Electron - Joshua Koo  What I've learn building a space visualization app with electron. • What's Happening with Service Workers - Apoorv Saxena Location: Microsoft AuditoriumOne Marina Boulevard,Level 21 Auditorium,Singapore 018989 , Singapore Remember to bring photo ID to get through building security. Feel free to ask questions in the SingaporeJS gitter room: https://gitter.im/SingaporeJS/discussions See you there!
events.location: Microsoft Auditorium (Singapore), One Marina Boulevard, Level 21 Auditorium, Singapore 018989

events.name: Hear from one of Australia's thought leaders on Product Management.
events.description: Nick Coster, co-founder of Brainmates is passionate about the benefits of putting the customer before the technology and building products and services that delight the buyer and the user. He's coming to the Neo Singapore HQ to talk about the core principles of product management and take questions from the audience. If we have time we'll then open the floor for a discussion. Nick is the head training facilitator for Brainmates so don't miss this opportunity to hear from one of the best. Nick has been developing and managing products for over 20 years, with range of different companies including Telstra BigPond, Excite@Home, Optus, Westpac and eBay, delivering internet service and telecommunications, online applications and internet security products. In the process of this journey he has developed a deep understanding of the way the different technologies fit together and is always amazed at the new and exciting ways that people use them.
